Program: Discovery
Title: Lifespan - slowing the ageing process
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrytc
Last Broadcast Date: 19 October 2004
The way creatures age and a look at whether lifespans can be extended. The programme interviews a 'life extensionist' who practices calorie restriction in order to live longer. Scientists are finding out more and more about one of life's biggest mysteries - the secrets of life, and death.